on the list were damaged in the Jan. 17 Northridge earthquake. "None of them 
appear to have any significant damage," he said. 
</P>
<P>
 Voters approved $250 million in bonds in 1990 for seismic strengthening of 
state buildings, and at the time authorities said the ranking of 14,000 state 
buildings would be completed in two years. But the process became mired in red 
