<HEADLINE>
<P>
DANIEL LEVINSON; PSYCHOLOGIST ADVANCED 'MALE MENOPAUSE' THEORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Daniel J. Levinson, 73, a psychologist who advanced the theory that men 
experience a menopause-like midlife crisis.Levinson taught at Yale University 
and its medical school from 1966 until he retired in 1990. He was principal 
author of the 1978 study "The Seasons of a Man's Life," which holds that males 
go through a series of developmental stages as they age, including an 
experience similar to menopause. Levinson recently completed a similar study 
dealing with females. "The Seasons of a Woman's Life" is to be published next 
year. In New Haven, Conn. on Tuesday of an apparent heart attack. 
