<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: PASADENA; 
FINGERPRINTING OF FEDERAL WELFARE APPLICANTS BEGINS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Applicants for a federal welfare program were fingerprinted for the first time 
this week under a program to fight fraud totaling hundreds of millions of 
dollars a year. 
</P>
<P>
 Welfare applicants were fingerprinted at Department of Public Social Services 
offices in Pasadena, Norwalk, Compton, Florence and West Los Angeles. The 
program involves the Aid to Families With Dependent Children program and will 
be expanded to other offices in coming weeks. Those refusing to be 
fingerprinted are denied aid. 
</P>
