<HEADLINE>
<P>
SMARTS IN AMERICA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Irish novelist Roddy Doyle seems surprised "that Hollywood always 
underestimates the audience's intelligence" ("He Talks the Talk -- Gaelic, That 
Is," March 23). Perhaps he is not familiar with the statement attributed to H. 
L. Mencken that "no one ever went broke underestimating the intelligence (or 
taste) of the American people." 
</P>
<P>
 JACK WRIGHT 
</P>
<P>
 Marina del Rey 
</P>
