<HEADLINE>
<P>
WAYS TO CARE FOR FINE LINENS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Careful, regular laundering will keep even the oldest and most cherished 
linens looking fresh. So, if they have to be washed, they might as well be 
enjoyed and used often. 
</P>
<P>
 Just remember that fine and heirloom linens should be handled with more care 
than everyday linens. Here are some tips: 
</P>
<P>
 * Place small items in a lingerie bag in the washing machine. 
</P>
<P>
 * If there is space, hang linens to dry. If not, use low heat in a clothes 
dryer and remove them while they are still slightly damp. 
</P>
<P>
 * While the linens are still damp, iron them on the wrong side. For extra 
delicate fabric, press over a towel. Shiny linens, such as damasks, should be 
ironed on the right side to bring up the shine. 
</P>
<P>
 * Hang table linens over a padded hanger or bar to avoid creases. Folded 
linens may develop a line along the folded edges, so refold them occasionally. 
Or, better yet, give a party and use them before laundering and refolding. 
</P>
</TEXT>
