<HEADLINE>
<P>
O.C. RELIGION NOTES / DAYE CLARK: CHURCH TO CELEBRATE ITS CENTENNIAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAYE CLARK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Interfaith Peace Ministry of Orange County will conduct its annual meeting 
and dinner on Sunday at Chapman University in Orange. In support of the United 
Nations 1994 International Year of the Family, the guest speaker will be family 
therapist Delores Wardell discussing "Building a Family Friendly Community." 
</P>
<P>
 The Paul Delp Peace Award will be presented to poet and activist Mitsuye 
Yamada. Yamada is a board member for Amnesty International, founder of the 
Multi-Cultural Women Writers and former chairperson of the Human Rights 
Commission in Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
 The meeting is from 5:30 to 8:30 p.m. in Room 209 of the Argyros building , 
333 N. Glassell St. The dinner is $15. For reservations, call the Interfaith 
Ministry at (714) 771-2901. 
</P>
</TEXT>
