<HEADLINE>
<P>
LEHMAN'S CAREER IS NO FAILURE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I strongly protest the characterization of Tom Lehman's career as one that 
"has been marked by failure" in your April 11 article on the conclusion of the 
Masters tournament. All he has done is persevere through the lean years in one 
of the most demanding of athletic occupations, earning more than a million 
dollars in the last two years, including more than 10 top-10 finishes and 
coming in third last year and second this year in the Masters. 
</P>
<P>
 It took a world-class golfer performing at the highest level to beat him in 
this year's tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 ALLEN MANN 
</P>
<P>
 Pacific Palisades 
</P>
</TEXT>
