<HEADLINE>
<P>
MANSELL LEADING A CHARMED LIFE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I've been an Indy car fan since I was a kid and I've never seen anybody get 
away with murder the way Nigel Mansell has. He won in Australia last year after 
passing the leader under yellow without penalty. 
</P>
<P>
 They black-flagged people last season more than in any other year, but Mansell 
didn't get penalized once. 
</P>
<P>
 It continues this year. He spun two or three times in Australia, once under 
yellow, but everybody praised his determination. Last week at Phoenix, he lost 
it in the warm-up lane, and except for Scott Goodyear's heads-up driving, he 
would have caused an accident as he entered the racing line before the merge 
line. 
</P>
<P>
 This is a blatant violation of the rules, but he was not penalized. It seems 
like they're constantly trying to hand this guy points on a silver platter. 
</P>
<P>
 I agree with Bobby Rahal, who said "Mansell's not God." I just wish the 
officials knew that. 
</P>
<P>
 PATRICK V. BOALES 
</P>
<P>
 Oxnard 
</P>
</TEXT>
