<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: OXNARD; ATTORNEY TO LEAD COLLEGE FOUNDATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A longtime Oxnard attorney has been named president of the Oxnard College 
Foundation, a nonprofit organization formed to support the college's 
educational programs. 
</P>
<P>
 Richard A. Regnier, who attended some of the first classes offered by Oxnard 
College in the early 1970s, takes over for Armando Lopez, who left the 
foundation earlier this year. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's a heavy responsibility and a very challenging task," Regnier said. "But 
I think we're in a position to accomplish some real good for Oxnard College." 
</P>
<P>
 Established in 1983, the Oxnard College Foundation is primarily a fund-raising 
group that appropriates money for student scholarships, educational programs 
and campus improvements. 
</P>
<P>
 Regnier has worked for the foundation since 1990 as both a director and 
general counsel. 
</P>
<P>
 Foundation board member Florence LaManno said Regnier has shown a dedication 
to the college as well as an ability to raise money from the private sector. 
</P>
<P>
 "He has a tremendous vision and a lot of capabilities," LaManno said. "He's 
spending a lot of time through his volunteerism to achieve the goals of both 
the college and the foundation." JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</TEXT>
