<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: NEWPORT BEACH; MURDER CHARGES FILED IN DEATH OF CHILD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FERNANDO ROMERO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 After a three-week investigation, authorities on Friday upgraded the charges 
against house painter Brian Laudenback to murder in the death of his 
girlfriend's 22-month-old son, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Laudenback, 32, of Newport Beach, had been charged last month with felony 
corporal punishment on a child after the death of Tyler Jaeger, the son of his 
girlfriend, Karey Jaeger, 22. 
</P>
<P>
 Laudenback was arrested after the child died March 25 at Hoag Hospital. A 
preliminary autopsy showed that the child, who was being baby-sat by 
Laudenback, had suffered severe blows to his liver and pancreas caused by a 
blunt instrument. 
</P>
<P>
 A week earlier the child had entered the same hospital with a large bump on 
his head that turned out to be a fractured skull. Laudenback said at the time 
that the child had fallen accidentally and hit his head. 
</P>
<P>
 Laudenback's arraignment, which was to occur Friday at Harbor Court, was 
postponed for unspecified reasons until next week, at which time he will be 
allowed to enter a plea on the new charge, said Newport Beach police spokesman 
Paul Henisey. 
</P>
<P>
 The arraignment date will be set Monday for Laudenback, whose bail was set at 
$250,000, Henisey said. FERNANDO ROMERO 
</P>
</TEXT>
