<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: OJAI; TOWER FOES TO HOLD BOWLING FUND-RAISER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TRACY WILSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ojai Valley opponents of a National Weather Service radar tower at Sulphur 
Mountain will host a celebrity bowling party Sunday at the Ojai Valley Bowl to 
raise money for the fight. 
</P>
<P>
 The residents who oppose the tower have lost a series of legal battles in 
recent months aimed at forcing the federal government to move the tower. 
</P>
<P>
 Proceeds from Sunday's bowling party will help pay about $11,000 in legal fees 
and help fund future events, said Dwier Brown, an organizer of the event. 
</P>
<P>
 Since the weather service erected the 98-foot-high weather-tracking system in 
November, homeowners have demanded its removal, saying the radar could cause 
health risks. 
</P>
<P>
 The bowling party will run from 3 to 7 p.m., with a $10 admission. 
Television's Scott Bakula of "Quantum Leap" will host the party, with stars 
Mary Steenburgen Rickie Lee Jones and Bill Paxton among those also scheduled to 
attend. 
</P>
<P>
 Tower opponents are also planning a $50 dinner and silent art auction -- to 
include two works donated by Ojai potter Beatrice Wood -- at 6:30 p.m. May 10 
at Wheeler Hot Springs, 1202 E. Ojai Ave., Ojai. For tickets, call 656-6656. 
TRACY WILSON 
</P>
