<P>
* JOHN R. ARTHUR; SHERIFF'S DEPUTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 John Russell Arthur, an eight-year veteran of the Ventura County Sheriff's 
Department, died Friday of cancer. He was 37. 
</P>
<P>
 Arthur was well-liked by his colleagues and the residents of Camarillo, whose 
streets he patrolled for nearly five years, Cmdr.Ray Abbott said. 
</P>
<P>
 "He just really loved his job and it showed," Abbott said. 
</P>
<P>
 Acquaintances described Arthur as a devoted family man. He is survived by his 
wife, Cheryl, and four children: Melissa, 14; Adam, 12; Kristi, 11, and 
Russell, 9. The Camarillo resident is also survived by his parents and brothers 
and sisters. 
</P>
<P>
 Abbott said the Sheriff's Department will have an honor guard at Arthur's 
funeral, scheduled for 1 p.m. Monday at the Camarillo Baptist Church. 
</P>
<P>
 Funeral arrangements are under the direction of Pierce Brothers Griffin 
Mortuary, Camarillo. 
