EAST VALLEY FOCUS: PACOIMA; ALARCON STAFFER TO LEAVE FOR KCBS POST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HUGO MARTIN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Los Angeles Councilman Richard Alarcon's director of communications is leaving 
at the end of April to become director of media relations for KCBS-TV, the 
councilman announced Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Sybil MacDonald, who has overseen Alarcon's media relations since August, said 
she will begin her new job in May.Prior to working for Alarcon, MacDonald 
worked for a video outlet firm designing a model for a Hispanic video store. 
</P>
<P>
 She has also worked as director of Hispanic public relations for a public 
relations firm and public relations director for KMEX-TV in Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
 MacDonald's departure is the third staff change Alarcon's office has undergone 
in his short tenure. In February, Alarcon hired Mayor Richard Riordan's press 
secretary, Annette Castro, to be his chief of staff in City Hall. In March, Leo 
Briones, an Alarcon deputy overseeing mail operations, quit to become vice 
president of a public relations firm in Woodland Hills. Briones has not been 
replaced. HUGO MARTIN 
</P>
