<TEXT>
<P>
 A Torrance man was killed when his motorcycle crashed into a pickup truck that 
had stopped at a four-way stop sign, authorities said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 The 23-year-old man was taken to Palmdale Hospital Medical Center, where he 
died. His identity was withheld until family members are notified. 
</P>
<P>
 The driver of the pickup was not hurt in the 11:05 p.m. crash, which occurred 
Thursday at Avenue P and 30th Street East, authorities said. 
