<HEADLINE>
<P>
JEFFIRES REJECTS RAMS' CONTRACT OFFER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE REILLEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Free-agent wide receiver Haywood Jeffires rejected the Rams' three-year, 
$3.9-million contract proposal Friday, choosing instead to entertain offers 
from other clubs, including his current team, Houston. 
</P>
<P>
 Jay Zygmunt, Ram senior vice president, confirmed Jeffires' decision, adding 
that the Rams do not plan to offer a new deal to the three-time Pro Bowl 
selection. 
</P>
<P>
 Jeffires, who earned $900,000 last season with Houston, has indicated he would 
like to stay with the Oilers. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The Rams signed free-agent defensive back and punt returner Cliff Hicks, 
formerly of the New York Jets. Hicks, 5 feet 10 and 187 pounds, was a 
third-round draft selection by the Rams in 1987. Hicks played three seasons 
with the Rams and three seasons with Buffalo before signing as a free-agent 
with the Jets last season. MIKE REILLEY 
</P>
</TEXT>
