<HEADLINE>
<P>
BASEBALL ROUNDUP; BRITO'S TWO-RUN SINGLE GIVES CYPRESS AN UPSET VICTORY OVER EL 
DORADO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Bobby Brito hit a two-run single in the top of the fifth inning to break a tie 
and lead Cypress to a 4-2 upset victory over El Dorado in an Empire League 
baseball game Friday at El Dorado High. 
</P>
<P>
 Brian Flanagan gave up two earned runs in seven innings to improve to 3-3 for 
Cypress (6-9-2, 1-6). Brito also had an RBI double in the fourth to help the 
Centurions tie the score, 2-2. 
</P>
<P>
 El Dorado's Spencer Frost hit a two-run home run in the second inning to give 
the Golden Hawks (13-5, 5-2) a 2-0 lead. Benny Flores gave up four earned runs 
in seven innings, falling to 3-4. 
</P>
<P>
 In another Empire League game: 
</P>
<P>
 Katella 6, Esperanza 1 -- Jaret Wright went three for four with a home run and 
two doubles for Katella (11-6, 5-2). Esperanza is 6-8, 3-4. 
</P>
