 Buena Park 7, Sonora 2 -- Ryan Glenn hit his first two home runs of the 
season, a three-run shot in the fourth and a bases-empty in the sixth for Buena 
Park (9-6, 5-2). Johnny Cabral had two hits, an RBI and one run scored and Greg 
Cabral had a two-run homer in the third. 
</P>
<P>
 Danny Baca pitched a complete game, giving up four hits and striking out 
seven. 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton 7, Sunny Hills 6 -- Steve St. Pierre hit a two-run home run and Ryan 
Schatz added a home run in the three-run sixth inning to help rally Fullerton 
(14-3, 6-1). 
</P>
<P>
 Troy 12, La Habra 9 (9 innings) -- La Habra committed three errors to open the 
top of the ninth, then Brian Logan hit a two-run single to spark a three-run 
inning for visiting Troy (11-5, 4-3). Logan had three hits and four RBIs. La 
Habra's Donny Cisneros hit a grand slam in the bottom of the sixth to tie the 
score. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Garden Grove League: 
</P>
<P>
 Bolsa Grande 2, Kennedy 1 -- Shortstop Alex Francisco led Bolsa Grande (8-7, 
4-2) in its victory over the Fighting Irish at Kennedy. Francisco went four for 
four, scoring both runs. He stole second, third and home in the third inning to 
give Matadors the victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Garden Grove 6, Los Amigos 1 -- Justin Lewis went three for three with an RBI 
for Garden Grove (8-7, 2-3). 
</P>
<P>
 La Quinta 2, Rancho Alamitos 1 (8 innings) -- C.J. Livernois' bases-loaded 
single with no outs in the bottom of the eighth to win it for seventh-ranked La 
Quinta (15-3, 6-0). 
</P>
<P>
 La Quinta's Joe Garcia (4-0) pitched a complete game, striking out 10 and 
walking none. 
</P>
<P>
 Pacifica 9, Santiago 8 -- Chad Brown had two hits and two RBIs to lead 
Pacifica (8-9, 2-3). 
</P>
<P>
 In the Orange League: 
</P>
<P>
 Brea-Olinda 12, Western 0 -- Bryan Robinson (5-2) struck out 12, giving up 
only three hits in a complete game for the sixth-ranked Wildcats. John Stoddard 
had two hits and three RBIs and Trevor Lords added three hits and one RBI for 
Brea-Olinda (15-2, 5-2). 
</P>
<P>
 Savanna 2, Magnolia 0 -- Russel Hartman (2-2) struck out six and gave up two 
hits for the complete-game shutout. Mike Hynes had an RBI single in the first 
inning for Savanna (6-11, 3-4). 
</P>
<P>
 In the Pacific Coast League: 
</P>
<P>
 Estancia 13, Costa Mesa 2 -- Jairo Arceyut had a two-run single, and Pedro 
Arceyut tripled him in to key an eight-run, third-inning rally for host 
Estancia (8-9, 4-3). 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Hills 6, Laguna Beach 3 -- The Hawks (7-8, 4-3) built a 5-0 lead after 
two innings at home and held off a late rally by Laguna Beach. Ryan Sauers hit 
his third home run of the season for the Artists (5-10, 1-6). 
</P>
<P>
 Trabuco Hills 8, Century 7 -- Brian Costello had a two-run single in a 
five-run third inning for Trabuco Hills (12-5, 7-0), which hung on for the 
victory. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Sea View League: 
</P>
<P>
 Corona del Mar 10, Newport Harbor 3 -- Chad Johnson hit a three-run homer and 
Jeff Bowman had three doubles and three RBIs for host Corona del Mar (13-4, 
4-2). Jim Huston was four for four for the Sea Kings. 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Margarita 6, Saddleback 1 -- Chris Collins and Curt Flore each had two 
hits for visiting Santa Margarita (9-7, 5-1). 
</P>
<P>
 In the Sunset League: 
</P>
<P>
 Edison 6, Santa Ana 0 -- Tom Barilla (2-1) gave up two hits in six innings, 
striking out five and walking one, for the victory at Edison. Barilla also 
drove in two runs. Todd Belitz had a two-run homer in the first inning and Greg 
Hanoian went two for two with a triple and two runs scored for the Chargers 
(13-4, 4-2). Lupe Alvarez took the loss for Santa Ana (0-6, 4-12). 
</P>
<P>
 Servite 4, Marina 2 -- Ross Miedecke struck out five and gave up two earned 
runs to lead Servite. Kevin Krotz had one hit and two RBIs and John Goldsmith 
had one hit and scored two runs for Servite. 
