<TEXT>
<P>
 Heather Meyer pitched Antelope Valley College into a first-place tie with 
Foothill Conference rival Chaffey by pitching a one-hitter, leading the 
Marauders to a 2-1 softball victory over the Panthers on Friday at Lancaster. 
</P>
<P>
 Meyer (14-4) had a no-hitter through 6 2/3 innings and struck out 13.The 
sophomore from Quartz Hill High also doubled and scored what proved to be the 
winning run in the fourth inning. 
</P>
<P>
 Yvette Allen had an RBI single in the third inning for the Marauders (29-7, 
7-1 in conference play). 
</P>
<P>
 Canyons 3-5, Pierce 0-3 -- Mary Ann Winchester picked up a victory and a save 
in the same afternoon as Canyons swept Pierce in a Western State Conference 
doubleheader at Valencia. 
</P>
<P>
 Winchester pitched a complete game, striking out five, and Kim Guerrero added 
three hits for Canyons in the first game. Winchester, who had three victories 
this week, picked up her first save of the season when she halted a Pierce 
rally in the seventh inning of the second game. BASEBALL 
</P>
