<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY ALL-STAR FOOTBALL GAME; DRAFT AMONG THOSE NAMED TO ROSTER FOR 
NORTH'S SQUAD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Chris Draft of Valencia High, The Times Orange County back of the year, is 
among 36 players on the North team roster for the 35th Orange County 
North-South All-Star Football Game. 
</P>
<P>
 Draft, who signed a letter of intent to play football at Stanford, gained 
1,338 yards rushing and scored 24 touchdowns to lead Valencia to the Orange 
League title and the semifinals of the Southern Section Division VI playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
 He finished with 3,038 yards in his three-year varsity career, but started at 
running back only two seasons. On defense, the 6-foot-2, 210-pound linebacker 
was third on the team in tackles and had nine sacks. 
</P>
<P>
 Los Alamitos (14-0), which won its second consecutive Division II championship 
last fall, leads all North participants with four players on the roster: 
quarterback Mike Good, offensive lineman Brad Hakala, defensive lineman Steve 
Trammell and linebacker Marc Albert. 
</P>
<P>
 Fred DiPalma will coach the North on July 8 at Orange Coast College. DiPalma 
led Savanna to the Division VI title. NORTH ROSTER 
</P>
<P>
 OFFENSE 
</P>
<P>
 Quarterbacks -- Mike Good (Los Alamitos), Paul Waldrop (Savanna). 
</P>
<P>
 Running backs -- Denis Dawson (Loara), Chris Draft (Valencia), George McDonald 
(Buena Park). 
</P>
<P>
 Tight end -- Mike Boomsma (Loara). 
</P>
<P>
 Receivers -- Craig Borsari (Sunny Hills), Josh Christensen (Western), Keith 
Ginter (Fullerton), Rani Kahouch (Savanna). 
</P>
<P>
 Linemen -- Erik Cecil (Whittier Christian), Dave Gillanders (Brea-Olinda), 
Brad Hakala (Los Alamitos), Matt Hertzler (El Dorado), Matt Marcyan (El 
Modena), Jeremiah Ross (Rancho Alamitos), Wali Sibrie (Buena Park), Terry 
Williams (El Dorado). 
</P>
<P>
 Kicker/Punter -- Jason Covarrubias (Western). DEFENSE 
</P>
<P>
 Linemen -- Gary DePhillips (Valencia), Steve Howard (Anaheim), Darryl Jones 
(Brethren Christian), Justin McCully (Villa Park), Steve Trammell (Los 
Alamitos), Dustin Williams (El Modena). 
</P>
<P>
 Linebackers -- Marc Albert (Los Alamitos), Javier Gomez (Anaheim), Adam 
Maldonado (Rancho Alamitos), Jim Stewart (Esperanza), Keith Washington 
(Brethren Christian). 
</P>
<P>
 Defensive backs -- Reggie Davis (Brethren Christian), Wesley Morris (Kennedy), 
Grant Pearsall (Villa Park), Gunnar Strunz (Canyon), Juan Viramontes (Katella), 
Jeff Williams (Orange). 
</P>
