<HEADLINE>
<P>
GOLDEN WEST CO-COACH DAVE STRICKLIN LEAVES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dave Stricklin, co-coach of the Golden West College women's basketball team 
the last eight years, has accepted a teaching and head coaching position at 
Umpqua College in Roseburg, Ore., a Golden West spokesman announced Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Stricklin, who with his father, Dick, has a record of 259-27 (.906) in guiding 
Golden West to the State tournament in each of the last eight seasons.The 
Rustlers advanced to the semifinals seven times and the championship game three 
times, winning unprecedented back-to-back State championships in 1990 and '91. 
</P>
<P>
 Last year, Golden West was 33-5 and won its fifth consecutive Orange Empire 
Conference title before losing to Los Angeles Harbor in the State title game. 
</P>
<P>
 "I'm excited about going, but I'm not excited about leaving," Dave Stricklin, 
35, said in a release. "I have had the opportunity to be in kind of a special 
situation the last several years working with my dad and I will really miss 
that." 
</P>
<P>
 Golden West also announced that Elizabeth Sirchia, a Kodak All-American who 
led the Rustlers to their consecutive State titles, will rejoin the school's 
program, replacing Dave Stricklin as assistant coach. 
</P>
<P>
 Sirchia, who was a two-time All-State and all-conference selection at Golden 
West, transferred to Hawaii, where she was a member of the Rainbow Wahine team 
that finished 25-7 and second in the Women's NIT. She later transferred to Cal 
Poly Pomona, where she played this season and was a first-team All-California 
College Athletic Assn. selection. 
</P>
<P>
 She will work with the Rustlers' guards and defense and be involved with 
recruiting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
