<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOR THE RECORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 No pandering arrest -- In articles published March 16 and 20 that mentioned 
the Redwood Inn Motel, The Times erroneously reported that a Los Angeles police 
officer testified at a public hearing that a motel manager was arrested on 
pandering charges.In fact, the officer did not specify the charge. The officer 
has since told The Times that a person affiliated with the hotel, but not the 
manager, was arrested on a misdemeanor charge. He declined to name the person. 
An attorney for the motel said the manager never has been arrested on any 
charge, and that no other motel employee has been arrested on charges related 
to prostitution. 
</P>
</TEXT>
